This paper proposes a new type of normalizing flow for flexible variational inference of posteriors over latent variables. The paper focuses on machine learning and neural networks, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The paper also discusses experiments on natural images, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-category. The use of autoregressive neural networks suggests that it could belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of variational autoencoders, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of invertible transformations, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category.
